title: Ukraine says British and French missiles worked 'perfectly' in attack on Russian navy
description: Ukraine has confirmed that British and French cruise missiles - fired from either wing of a Ukrainian bomber - were used in a major attack against Russia's navy in occupied Crimea and worked "perfectly".

title: The horrifying moment a girl's body was found in a city flattened by floods
description: The centre of the eastern Libyan city of Derna is like one big graveyard - a mass of flattened buildings, wrecked lives and upended vehicles amid torn trees.

title: How the injustice of climate change set the stage for disaster in Libya
description: On the face of it there is a clear explanation for the tragedy in Derna.

title: Why beach cleans matter as new research gives scientists hope for polluted oceans
description: Beach cleans rapidly and dramatically reduce plastic fragments released into the environment, according to the first scientific evidence of its kind.

title: How a Libyan city was washed away
description: Rescuers are calling for more body bags to be sent to a Libyan city hit by catastrophic flooding - as fears of waterborne diseases grow.

title: The missed chances to save Libya's flood victims from disaster
description: Storm Daniel was Greece's worst storm in recorded history but for Libya it would trigger a disaster of unimaginable scale.

title: Man arrested over British woman's death in Spain
description: A pensioner has been arrested over the death of a British woman in Spain's Costa Blanca.

title: TikTok fined €345m over handling of children's data
description: TikTok has been fined €345m (£296m) for breaching privacy laws over the processing of children's personal data, an EU regulator has said.

title: 'Stalker' who barged into dressing room and yelled 'I want to marry Emma Watson' arrested
description: A man accused of repeatedly stalking celebrities has been arrested for barging into a dressing room at a New York City fashion show and screaming that he wanted to marry Emma Watson, police say.

title: Rubiales arrives at court for questioning over Hermoso kiss
description: Luis Rubiales has arrived at a Madrid court to be questioned by a judge investigating his kiss of Jenni Hermoso.

title: Libya's destroyed community - where people will 'never forget what happened here'
description: Locals now call Wadi Derna "the dam of death".

title: Gang hacked World Cup video feed to beat bookmakers
description: A global policing operation has dismantled an organised crime group which intercepted video signals from 2022 World Cup matches and other sporting events for speedy bets to gain an advantage on bookmakers.

title: Horror after body of young girl found - as UN warns of cholera outbreak risk
description: A potential cholera outbreak could add to misery in the Libyan city of Derna, where the sheer number of people dead or unaccounted for after a massive flood is overwhelming survivors.

title: Libya dams collapsing after deadly storm sounded like 'explosion after explosion'
description: The sheer numbers of people dead or unaccounted for in the Libyan city of Derna is overwhelming survivors, who say they had minutes to get away before the coastal city was devastated by a tsunami-like torrent.

title: 'They're trying to silence me': Iran theatens crackdown on anniversary of Mahsa Amini's death
description: "They killed my brother, and now they're coming for us too."
